# Smoke Test Catalog

Single registry for smoke tests and their operational purpose.

## Rules
- Every new core workflow requires at least one smoke test.
- Smoke tests should run in seconds and avoid expensive setup.
- Add catalog entries in the same change that introduces a new smoke test.

## Current Smoke Tests
| Test file | Purpose | Trigger command |
|---|---|---|
| `[SMOKE_TEST_PATH]` | Verifies startup/import baseline | `[SMOKE_COMMAND]` |

## Add a New Smoke Test
1. Create smoke scaffold (or equivalent generator command).
2. Implement a minimal pass/fail assertion.
3. Update this catalog row.
4. Run smoke command and verify gate.
